Package: cockpit-upside
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         cockpit-bridge
Recommends: nut-client
Description: UPS monitoring for Cockpit, powered by NUT
 UPSide surfaces the state of one or more UPS devices managed by NUT
 (Network UPS Tools) directly in the Cockpit web console: battery charge and
 runtime, line/load status, input/output voltage, and the other variables
 exposed by upsd. It supports multiple UPSes, with an overview of all devices
 and a detail view per device, optional historical trends from PCP, and a
 status indicator in the Cockpit navigation.
 .
 It is a read-only client of a running NUT setup and runs no backend service
 of its own; NUT's upsd is the backend. A working NUT installation (upsd
 running, at least one UPS in ups.conf) is required; install nut-client on
 this host (pulled in by the recommendation) or point it at a remote upsd.
